Once I learned the infrastructure was already there, it was just learning how to make Alert Rules on Grafana. 

Watching tutorials and trying them at the same time helped a lot. I made a server on Discord so that way I could test it out before I was given my account 
from Prof Bisesti.

First I had to set up a High CPU Alert Rule which consisted of: 
  - On the left sidebar under 'Alerting'
  - Click 'Alert Rules'
  - CLick 'New Alert Rule'
  - Name the Rule as 'High CPU Usage'
  - Select the folder to save it in which was 'Alerts' in the Dashboard
  - Set the 'Evaluation Group' to 'Rack Server'

Next Step was to Add the Code to the Query:
  - The Query code is: 100 - (avg by(instance)(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m])) * 100)
  - node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"} is a counter metric from Node Exporter that measures the total number of seonds the CPU has spent in a given mode.
    -{mode="idle"} filters the metric to only include idle CPU time
  - This part selects total accumulated seconds where CPU was idle

  - rate(...[5m]) calculates the per-second average increase over the last 5 minutes, since it is a counter it converts into the fraction of time
  the CPU was idle per second over a 5 minute period.

  - avg by(instance)(...)
    - Each CPU core reports separately
  - This part:
    - Averages the idle rate  
    - Groups the result by instance
    - Combines all CPU cores into a single value per machine
  - This gives you the average idle percentage per instance

  - *100 converts from decimal/fraction to percentage .72 -> 72
      - Idle = 72%
  - 100 - (...) flips idle into usage  
      - CPU Usage = 100-72 = 28%

Next Step is to set your Alert Conditions

  - You will see Expression -> Threshold
  - Warning Condition set to:
    - Name of Condition: High CPU Usage
    - WHEN: A
    - IS ABOVE: (Your desired percentage)
    - FOR: (Designated time interval) 
